3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"dYdX calculates FTM/USDT funding rates every hour using a time-weighted average of the premium/discount between perpetual and spot prices. The funding rate is exchanged between long and short position holders at the top of each hour, with positive rates paid by longs to shorts. dYdX's Cosmos-based architecture enables more frequent funding settlements compared to traditional 8-hour cycles. The platform's orderbook model provides transparent price discovery for accurate funding rate calculations."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","FTM","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"FTM/USDT represents strong arbitrage potential due to Fantom's active DeFi ecosystem creating periodic funding rate imbalances. The pair's mid-tier volume provides sufficient liquidity while avoiding the extreme competition found in major pairs. Fantom's correlation with broader L1 trends creates predictable funding patterns during market cycles, making it attractive for systematic arbitrage strategies."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical FTM Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"FTM funding rates on dYdX typically range from -0.01% to 0.02% during normal market conditions, with significant spikes during Fantom ecosystem developments. The token shows strong correlation with DeFi sector performance, often experiencing elevated funding rates during yield farming trends or protocol launches. Historical data reveals FTM funding tends to turn negative during broader market downturns as traders short L1 tokens. The 1-hour funding frequency on dYdX allows for more granular capture of these rate movements compared to traditional 8-hour cycles."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities and Execution"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Cross-exchange arbitrage between dYdX FTM/USDT and other major exchanges becomes profitable when funding rate differentials exceed 0.015% per hour after accounting for trading fees. The Cosmos appchain's lower gas costs compared to Ethereum-based DEXs improve arbitrage economics significantly. Market makers can exploit funding rate premiums during Fantom network upgrades or major DeFi protocol launches when sentiment diverges across platforms. Position sizing should account for dYdX's reduced liquidity post-migration while maintaining adequate capital efficiency."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations and Platform Specifics"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"dYdX's post-migration lower volumes create increased slippage risks for larger FTM/USDT positions compared to the platform's StarkEx era. Smart contract risks associated with the new Cosmos appchain implementation require careful consideration despite the platform's established track record. FTM's correlation with Fantom network performance adds specific fundamental risks during validator issues or network congestion. Traders must monitor both technical analysis signals and Fantom ecosystem developments to effectively manage funding rate arbitrage positions."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How does dYdX's 1-hour funding affect FTM arbitrage strategies?","answer":"The 1-hour funding intervals on dYdX provide 8 times more settlement opportunities compared to traditional platforms, allowing traders to capture short-term FTM funding rate spikes. This frequency is particularly beneficial for FTM given its volatility around Fantom ecosystem events."},{"question":"What are the main liquidity considerations for FTM/USDT on dYdX?","answer":"Post-migration liquidity is lower than dYdX's StarkEx era, typically supporting positions up to $50,000 without significant slippage. Traders should monitor order book depth during Fantom network events when volume can spike dramatically."},{"question":"How do Fantom network developments impact funding rates?","answer":"Major Fantom protocol launches, validator updates, or DeFi partnerships often create temporary funding rate imbalances as sentiment shifts. These events typically generate 2-4 hour windows of elevated funding rates before normalizing."},{"question":"What makes FTM funding rates different from other L1 tokens on dYdX?","answer":"FTM shows stronger correlation with DeFi sector performance rather than pure L1 infrastructure trends, creating unique funding patterns. The token's mid-tier volume provides optimal conditions for arbitrage without excessive competition from institutional traders."}]}]
